 :Section ‚ćĚ Update list of events to emulate here
     :If myevent‚Č°'Event' ‚ćĚ Are we setting up a pure Dyalog event?
         ‚ćĚ? This process hasn't been written yet, but works entirely differently than APL+Win events
     :Else
         :If sys~‚ćõ‚ąß0=‚ČĘarg ‚ćĚ Are they disabling an event?
             pseudo~‚Üź‚äāmyevent ‚ćĚ Remove the name from the list to process (if it's the last one, just leave the argument empty)
         :ElseIf myevent‚äā‚ćõ‚ąäpseudo
         ‚ćĚ It's already here - leave it alone
             :Return ‚ćĚ We don't need to update anything in the GUI
         :ElseIf sys ‚ćĚ If this is a system-level event, always put it at the beginning
             pseudo‚Üźpseudo‚ą™‚ć®‚äā':',myevent
         :Else
             bat‚Üź‚Ćä/(1+‚ČĘpseudo),pseudo‚ć≥before ‚ćĚ Where are any before parameters?
             aat‚Üź‚Ćą/0,(1+‚ČĘpseudo)|pseudo‚ć≥after ‚ćĚ Where are any after parameters?
             'Cannot satisfy positioning requirements'‚éēSIGNAL 11/‚ć®bat‚Č§aat
             :If bat>‚ČĘpseudo ‚ćĚ There were no "before" parameters
                 :If aat=0 ‚ćĚ There were no "after" parameters
                     pseudo,‚Üź‚äāmyevent ‚ćĚ Just append it to the end
                 :Else ‚ćĚ We have only "after" parameters
                     pseudo‚Üź(aat‚ÜĎpseudo),(‚äāmyevent),aat‚Üďpseudo ‚ćĚ Put it right after the required parameter (since they're likely to be related)
                 :EndIf
             :Else ‚ćĚ We have "before" parameters
                 :If aat=0 ‚ćĚ But no "after" parameters
                     pseudo‚Üź(pseudo‚ÜĎ‚ć®bat-1),(‚äāmyevent),pseudo‚Üď‚ć®bat-1 ‚ćĚ Insert new event at (the last) acceptable position
                 :Else ‚ćĚ We also have "after" parameters
                     pseudo‚Üź(aat‚ÜĎpseudo),(‚äāmyevent),aat‚Üďpseudo ‚ćĚ Put it right after the required parameter (but could just as easily go at the other end)
                 :EndIf
             :EndIf
         :EndIf
     :EndIf
 :EndSection

